data.name: radComObj.ToolTip
data.value: In "Common Objects" mode, objects are only shown if that object exists in every selected device, with a). the same instance number and b). the part of the object name after the final delimeter matches. E.g. if delimeter is set to apostrophe, "Rm1'Temp" matches with "Rm2'Temp", but "Rm1'Temp" and "Rm1'Hum" do not match.

data.name: oComProp.ToolTip
data.value: In "Properties Common to ALL" mode, properties are only listed if ALL of the selected points have the property in their property list. Additionally, the Bacnet Application Tag must match between all properties unless it is the priority array (which is excluded from this condition), and any other array properties must have the same length.

data.name: oAnyProp.ToolTip
data.value: In "Properties that Exist in ANY" mode, any property that is present in ANY of the selected points will make it into the property list, ignoring Bacnet Application Tag and array size. Note that "Globally Command" must be disabled in this case, to avoid the risk of accidentally commanding two different data typed points to the same value. E.g. we don't want to Globally Command an analog value and a binary value both to 22.5, because the binary value commands would fail in this case.
